      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 355: 🔴 Critical Issues - The audio congestion callback is invoked every RTCP check while loss stays above 3%, even when this is a receive-side impairment that reducing local video bitrate may not fix. In a bidirectional call this can unnecessarily throttle all local video streams because the code couples remote audio receive loss directly to local video send bitrate. Gate this on sender-side congestion evidence, or document and implement the intended directionality explicitly so only the video stream sharing the congested uplink is reduced.\n```suggestion\n// Only trigger audio-\u003evideo coupling for congestion affecting this endpoint\u0027s outgoing media,\n// or pass direction/context into the callback and reduce the matching video sender only.\n```",
      "revId": "390e4a7d2879540ce66325a1ed5f1a46e326b746",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
