      "message": "Line 54: 🟡 Suggestions - `shouldSend()` sleeps on the media send path to simulate jitter. This can block encoder/RTP threads and alter application timing well beyond packet-level simulation, especially with multiple streams. Prefer queueing delayed packets in a simulator-owned worker, or keep this simulator limited to unit tests behind a test-only build flag.\n```suggestion\n// Instead of sleeping here, enqueue the packet with a target send time and let a simulator worker release it later.\n```",
