      "message": "Line 131: 🟡 Suggestions - The script appends iptables ACCEPT rules but only deletes one matching rule on teardown. If setup is interrupted after partial state changes or duplicate rules already exist, rules can be left behind. Use `iptables-save`/restore for the previous state, or delete in a loop until no matching rule remains.\n```suggestion\nwhile iptables -D FORWARD -i ${BR_A} -o ${BR_B} -j ACCEPT 2\u003e/dev/null; do :; done\nwhile iptables -D FORWARD -i ${BR_B} -o ${BR_A} -j ACCEPT 2\u003e/dev/null; do :; done\n```",
